<br>
I am only level 51 and been working on my epic. Thus far i had been unable to get in on another guilds PoH raid and our guild doesn't do PoH much anymore.<br>
<br>
So last night i convinced a level 60 wiz to port my nekked ass up to PoH then gate out... There i was, totally alone in a fully popped plane with only a thurgadin gate potion and some food and water on me. Thanks to the information that many others here have passed along, i made my way past 3 scorned banshee's and 3 loathing lich's up to the 2nd floor of Maestro's house. Sneaking and hiding the whole way i found my way over to the bedroom and grabbed my Book of Souls. I picked it up and was heading back to a safe spot i had found earlier in order to gate out....<br>
<br>
And then Innoruk himself decided to hit me 4 times for 401pts of damage per hit... sneak and hide were off, innoruks next hit was coming any second, and i ran as fast as i could (only buff i had on was SoW) and stopped and used my thurgadin gate potion.... that was the longed 45 minute casting time potion i have ever seen. My heart was literally throbbing out of my chest... then i saw the &quot;Loading, please wait&quot;.... I sat there with a dumbstruck look in my eyes...... <br>
<br>
had i gated out ok?<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
Had Innoruk taken the last of my hp with a single final swing?<br>
<br>
I zoned into Thurg on the bridge with 4hp and the book of souls in my inventory.<br>
<br>
In over a year of playing, that was THE most sphincter tightening thing i have ever done. It probably pales in comparison to many peoples adventures, but having a 57 cleric as your main doesn't lend itself to harrowing experiences, especially solo.<br>
<br>
Thanks to the info my rogue peers provided, i was able to pull it off.<br>
<br>
/bow<br>
